feedback.query: why america is more developed country than india?
feedback.response: India has been developing its economy in recent years due to its vast natural resources, favorable location, and large population. As of 2019, India was the world's second-largest economy by nominal GDP, with a Gross Domestic Product (GDP) per capita of $13,865 compared to $7,473 in China. In terms of GDP per capita, India also leads the world in the manufacturing sector, accounting for nearly 25% of global output. Additionally, India has a high standard of living and a growing middle class, which contribute to its economic growth.
